#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Clusters"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:6
msgid ""
"You can use {productname} to directly manage {caasp} clusters.  Manage "
"clusters that you have registered with {productname} by navigating to menu:"
"Clusters[Overview] in the {webui}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Autoinstallation Profile"
msgstr ""

#. For more information about the profile, see https://documentation.suse.com/suse-caasp/4.2/single-html/caasp-deployment/#_autoyast_preparation.
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:14
msgid ""
"{caasp}{nbsp}4 provides an AutoYaST profile that you can use to autoinstall "
"a node.  The profile is in the ``patterns-caasp-Management`` package."
msgstr ""

#. For an example script based based on the {caasp}{nbsp}4 template, customized to make use of {productname}, see xref:client-configuration:caasp-autoinstallation-example.adoc[].
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:20
msgid ""
"You can use {productname} to manage one or more existing {caasp} clusters."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:24
msgid "Only {caasp}{nbsp}4 is currently supported."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:28
msgid "Before you begin, ensure you have installed your {caasp} cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "Elect a Management Node"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:36
msgid ""
"To manage a {caasp} cluster, you need to elect a client as the management "
"node for the cluster.  The management node cannot be part of the cluster, "
"and it must have the {caasp} channels associated with it before you begin.  "
"You can use a single management node for multiple clusters, as long as the "
"clusters are all of the same kind."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Electing a Management Node"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:41
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[System List] and "
"click the name of the client to elect as the management node."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:42
msgid ""
"Navigate to the menu:Formulas[Configuration] tab, and check the ``CaaSP "
"Management Node`` formula."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:43
msgid "Click btn:[Save] and apply the highstate."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:48
msgid "Do not use the management node until the highstate has been completed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:55
msgid ""
"List all known clusters by navigating to menu:Clusters[Overview].  This list "
"displays all existing clusters, along with the cluster type, and which "
"management node they are associated with.  It also shows the nodes within "
"the cluster, if the nodes are registered to {productname}.  For the nodes "
"within a cluster, additional information from ``skuba`` and the {k8s} API "
"are shown, including the role, status, and whether any updates are available."
msgstr ""

#. For more information about the data available for nodes, see //https://documentation.suse.com/suse-caasp/4/html/caasp-admin/#_cluster_updates.html.
#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Configuring the Management Node"
msgstr ""

#.  Default file location? --LKB 2020-06-04
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:65
msgid ""
"Copy the ``skuba`` configuration directory from your cluster to the "
"management node.  This is the directory that the ``skuba`` service creates "
"after the cluster has been bootstrapped.  Take a note of the new file "
"location for adding the cluster in the {productname} {webui}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:66
msgid "Provide a way to authenticate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:68
msgid ""
"There are two ways you can authenticate a {caasp} cluster, choose the method "
"that best suits your environment:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:71
msgid ""
"Copy the passwordless private SSH key used to access the cluster nodes to "
"the {productname} Server, and take a note of the file location.  You need "
"the current keys and keys for any clients that you want to use in the future."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:72
msgid ""
"You can use an ``ssh-agent`` socket, and provide the path to the socket when "
"setting up the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:75
msgid ""
"There are two ways of using the ``ssh-agent`` with {caasp}.  You can use "
"``ssh-agent`` locally, or forward the `ssh-agent` to the management node "
"from another machine:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Using a Local ssh-agent"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:80
msgid ""
"On the management node, at the command prompt, start the ``ssh-agent`` "
"service:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "eval $(ssh-agent)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:85
msgid "Add the SSH key:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "ssh-add <key>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:90
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:100
msgid ""
"The socket used to access the agent is available in the ``$SSH_AUTH_SOCK`` "
"environment variable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Forwarding ssh-agent to the Management Node"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:95
msgid ""
"On the system that is providing ``ssh-agent``, at the command prompt, enable "
"SSH forwarding, and specify the hostname of the management node:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "ssh -A <management node>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:107
msgid ""
"If you are using the ``ssh-agent`` method, the path of the socket changes "
"every time a new ``ssh-agent``` is started or a new ``ssh -A`` connection is "
"started.  The ``ssh-agent`` socket path can be updated at any time from the "
"{productname} {webui}.  The socket path can also be overridden when starting "
"any cluster action that requires SSH access."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manage Clusters"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:114
msgid "To manage a cluster in {productname}, add the cluster in the {webui}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Adding an Existing Cluster"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:119
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Clusters[Overview] and click "
"btn:[Add]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:120
msgid ""
"Follow the prompts to provide information about your cluster, including the "
"cluster type, and select the management node to associate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:121
msgid "Type the path to the ``skuba`` configuration file for the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:122
msgid ""
"Type the passwordless SSH key you want to use, or provide the path to an "
"``ssh-agent`` socket."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:123
msgid "Type a name, label, and description for the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:124
msgid "Click btn:[Add]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:130
msgid ""
"For each cluster you manage with {productname}, a corresponding system group "
"is created.  By default, the system group is called ``Cluster "
"<cluster_name>``.  Refresh the system group to update the list of nodes.  "
"Only nodes known to {productname} are shown."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:133
msgid ""
"You can remove clusters from {productname} by navigating to menu:"
"Clusters[Overview], unchecking the cluster to be deleted, and clicking btn:"
"[Delete Cluster]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:139
msgid ""
"Deleting a cluster removes the cluster from {productname}, it does not "
"delete the cluster nodes.  Workloads running on the cluster will continue "
"uninterrupted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:143
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manage Nodes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:146
msgid ""
"When you have the cluster created in {productname}, you can manage nodes "
"within the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:148
msgid ""
"Before you add a new node to the cluster, check the management node can "
"access the node you want to add using passwordless SSH, or the ``ssh-agent`` "
"socket you are forwarding."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:150
msgid ""
"You also need to ensure that the node you want to add is registered to "
"{productname}, and has a {caasp} channel assigned."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:154
msgid ""
"Before you add a node to a cluster, you might need to do some manual "
"configuration.  Check that the system is used exclusively as a {caasp} node, "
"and that swap is turned off.  For more information, see https://"
"documentation.suse.com/suse-caasp/4.2/single-html/caasp-deployment/"
"#_disabling_swap"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Adding Nodes to a Cluster"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:159
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Clusters[Overview] and click "
"btn:[Join Node]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:161
msgid ""
"Select the nodes to add from the list of available nodes.  The list of "
"available nodes includes only nodes that are registered to {productname}, "
"are not management nodes, and are not currently part of any cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:162
msgid ""
"Follow the prompts to enter the {caasp} parameters for the nodes to be added."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:163
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: Specify a custom ``ssh-agent`` socket that is valid only for the "
"nodes that are being added."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:164
msgid ""
"Click btn:[Save] to schedule an action to add the nodes to the {caasp} "
"cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:167
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Removing Nodes from a Cluster"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:169
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Clusters[Overview], uncheck "
"the nodes to remove, and click btn:[Remove Node]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:170
msgid ""
"Follow the prompts to define the parameters for the nodes to be removed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:171
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: Specify a custom ``ssh-agent`` socket that is valid only for the "
"nodes that are being removed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:172
msgid "Click btn:[Save] to schedule an action to remove the nodes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:174
msgid ""
"For more information about node removal, see https://documentation.suse.com/"
"suse-caasp/4/single-html/caasp-admin/#_permanent_removal."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:177
#, no-wrap
msgid "Upgrade Clusters"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:180
msgid ""
"If the cluster has available updates, you can use {productname} to schedule "
"and manage the upgrade."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:183
msgid ""
"{productname} upgrades all control planes first, and then upgrades the "
"workers.  For more information, see https://documentation.suse.com/suse-"
"caasp/4.2/single-html/caasp-admin/#_cluster_updates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Upgrading the Cluster"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:187
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Clusters[Overview], and click "
"the cluster to upgrade."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:189
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: The are no {caasp} parameters available for you to customize for "
"upgrade.  However, you can specify a custom ``ssh-agent`` socket that is "
"valid only for the nodes that are being upgraded."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:190
msgid "Click btn:[Save] to schedule an action to upgrade the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:196
msgid ""
"{productname} will only interact with ``skuba`` to upgrade the cluster.  Any "
"other required action, such as configuration changes, are not issued by "
"{productname}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clusters.adoc:199
msgid ""
"For more information about upgrading, see https://www.suse.com/releasenotes/"
"x86_64/SUSE-CAASP/4."
msgstr ""
